cs.NI, cs.SD, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DC

The paper discusses the evolution of network management in the context of software-defined networking and network functions virtualization, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a framework for service provider DevOps, which involves software development practices for network operations, and thus could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses challenges in service verification, observability, and troubleshooting, which could be categorized under software-defined networking (cs.SD) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses carrier-grade operations and management, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
